    "Id": "219956",
    "ThreadId": "64604",
    "Html": "<p>I think I see what's happening. In SL the&nbsp;TabControlRegionAdapter.TabControlRegionSyncBehaviour.GetDataContext() is setting the DataContext of the TabItem to the DataContext of the View, rather than the View itself. This is inconsistent with the WPF approach, which doesn't have a similar adapter, and simply binds the View to the TabItem.</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-08-05T12:40:21.843-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "220106",
    "ThreadId": "64604",
    "Html": "<p>OK, so for experimental purposes I changed the TabControlRegionAdapter.TabControlRegionSyncBehaviour.GetDataContext() to return the View (FrameworkElement) instead of the Model (FrameworkElement.DataContext), and the StockTraderRI still seems to&nbsp;work just fine in SL. I take it that the restriction on not being able to use a FrameworkElement as a DataContext was removed between SL2 and SL3?</p>\r\n<p>Anyone know for sure?</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-08-05T19:34:26.767-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  }
